stylometry: The advantages of simulation models is that it immitates real life situations by putting in uncertaintity with input variables and getting random values that vary. It shows and entire distribution of results and not just a single outcome. It is useful because it shows different results for different sittuations. It answers what if questions without actually having to have a physical outcome. You would use simulations in a management or business situation because you can see what the outcome of something will be before having to spend the money to go ahead with it in your company. Also running a simulation may find you the best answer to what you are trying to do.
